Attention Before Purchasing: 1. About Compatibility This usb c hub supports Most Type-C devices, but please notes that the USB C port of your host is required to support data, charging and video (DP Alt Mode) 2. About using ports at the same time All ports can be used simultaneously.However, due to the performance limitations of some laptops, it's recommended to avoid connecting peripherals that requires more than 900mA start-up current. Please only connect one hard drive / SSD at a time 3. About being hot When the usb c hub is fully loaded, its surface may reach 149°F, which is normal for an aluminum shell usbc hub to dissipate heat and keep running properly 4. About interference with WIFI signal According to Microsoft, USB 3.0 may be affected by 2.4GHz Wi-Fi. It is suggested that you set your Wi-Fi frequency to 5GHz to avoid this problem

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just what I needed
reviews.reviewText: I've tried other adapters to read my SD cards to upload my photos when I do photoshoots and this one is the best one I've used. I have a MACBOOK AIR and it plugs right into the USB-C port and works like a charm. It has two USB ports to plug my external hard drive, an HDMI port, an SD port & a mini SD port.If you have a MACBOOK AIR and need to upload photos, this is the one you should use. It's compact and stores great in the grey pouch included. I haven't used it for traveling yet, but I'm sure it won't take up too much room in my carry on.

reviews.reviewText: I just bought a new computer. I couldn't plug my back up hard drive in with new ports. This little adapter is perfect and you can plug a few things into it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
Reviewed in the United States on June 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Exactly what I needed!
reviews.reviewText: My new Mac Mini has only two USB 3 ports. I use one for my keyboard/mouse receiver and the other for my outboard drive. I need more USB 3's for other uses. This adaptor plugs into my Thunderbolt C port and gives me 3 USB 3's, as well as SD and MiniSD ports, an HDMI port and a USB PD 100W. charging port. So far, It works flawlessly. It's not bad looking and the size is just right.The price is right.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Constantly Unplugging & Replugging USB Devices
reviews.reviewText: I use this to connect my laptop to an external monitor, webcam, keyboard & mouse. No matter what USB spot I plug it into, I have to constantly unplug my keyboard to reconnect it. I will be typing and it will just randomly stop. Now all of a sudden its doing the same thing for my webcam. I thought the device I've had since May was just defective (it's done it this whole time and I've just been lazy and dealt with it) but now that its starting to cause issues with my webcam its even more of a hassle. I bought a new one hoping it would work fine and there was just an issue with the original one I purchased but I had the same issue right off the bat. Very frustrating and not at all worth the money.

reviews.reviewTitle: 7 in 1 USB hub, strong and sturdy
reviews.reviewText: 7 in 1 USB hub, strong and sturdy. HDMI 4K + SD/TF card slots for direct card reading makes it great choice. 90W output is great as it can be used with majority of laptopns including my Macbook Pro.Three USB3 and one USB C works well to connect external mouse and keyboard to my Macbook.I did notice that my monitor reset (one second flicker made the screen go off and back on) when connected my 4k Samsung monitor to Macbook, however when connected to windows computer it was smooth and no issues.Overall a good choice especially for Windows users.

reviews.reviewTitle: Not great in terms of Build Quality!
reviews.reviewText: This is a good-to-have item for laptop users, especially MacBook Pro users where there are minimal ports. All ports work as expected. It certainly doesn't replace a more expensive docking station given the short length of the USB-C cable and the fact that it only has two USB-A ports. My only concern is with the design, not as heavy as I want it to be.
